But behold! It has room enough for —in it,

hundreds and thousands,—all the

varieties;

There is an old Egyptian temple

—and again, a Greek temple,

of white marble;

Wisdom undisturbed, self-respect,

fortitude unshaken, are in his

expression, his personality;

He shows how independent one may

be of fortune—how triumphant

over fate;

—And here, (for I have all kinds,) here

is Columbus setting sail from

Spain on his voyage of discovery;

This is the queen on her way to

the scaffold—those are guil-

lotines;

And now a merry recruiter passes, with

fife and drum, seeking who

will join his troop;

—And there are wood-cutters, cutting

down trees in my the north-east woods—see

you, the axe uplifted;

This, again, is a Spanish bull-fight—

see, the animal with bent head,

fiercely advancing;

And there are flowers and fruits—

see you, the grapes, decked off

with vine-leaves;

And there an Arab caravan, halting—

See you, the palm trees, the camels,

and the stretch of hot sand far away;;

And here is an my Oregon hunting‑hut,

with a hunter see me emerging from

the door, carrying bearing his my rifle in his my hand;;

But there, see you, a reminiscence from over sea—

a very old Druid, walking the

