And there, singular, on ocean waves,

downward, buoyant, swift, over

the waters, an occupied coffin floating;

And there hang painted scenes from

my Kansas life—and there from

what I saw in the Lake Superior region;

As from a thick haze, more dumb

and thick than ever rose ever rose any rising from

vapor above the hot sea;

